Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine light pink-brown; grey core. Rectangular stamp with bee symbol.
Type series: KT568 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Names, Epiphanes. Karneodotos. Trimmed. A piece in the Benaki collection, Alexandria Museum, is from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0329)
